# CONTEXT.md Template

> Referenced by: begin skill (Step 9c), discuss skill, plan skill
> Created during /pbr:new-project. Updated by /pbr:discuss-phase and /pbr:plan-phase --assumptions.

## Structure

```markdown
# Phase Context

**Created by:** {skill}
**Date:** {date}

## Decision Summary

<!-- Compact digest for agent prompt injection. ~300 tokens max. -->

<domain>
{Problem domain context -- what this phase is about, key terminology, system boundaries}
</domain>

<decisions>
{Locked decisions from discuss. NON-NEGOTIABLE during planning.}

- [ ] **{Decision title}** -- {Description}
  - Scope: {RH-IDs}
  - Quality: {acceptance criteria}
  - Integration: {how it connects to other components}
</decisions>

<canonical_refs>
{Specs, ADRs, design docs, research files with FULL paths. Downstream agents MUST read these.}

- .planning/research/{file}.md -- {description}
- {other paths}
</canonical_refs>

<deferred>
{Ideas explicitly excluded from this phase. Plans MUST NOT include these.}

- **{Idea}** -- {Reason deferred}
</deferred>

## Claude's Discretion Areas

{Areas where the planner can make implementation choices without asking the user.
 Document the choice made and rationale when exercised.}

| Area | Choice Made | Rationale |
|------|------------|-----------|
| {e.g., "State management library"} | {e.g., "Zustand"} | {e.g., "Lightweight, fits project size"} |
```

## Rules

- Locked decisions are immutable once set -- only the user can change them
- Deferred ideas must NEVER appear in plans
- Discretion areas are documented when the planner exercises choice
- Phase-level CONTEXT.md files (in phase directories) override project-level for that phase
- Backward compatibility: existing CONTEXT.md files using markdown headers (## Decisions, ## Deferred Ideas) remain valid
